    <high>https://vid.tasty.co/output/33469/mp4_720x1280/1496770195</high>
  </video>
  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). </step>
    <step num="1">Grease a 9-inch (23 cm) cake pan with butter. </step>
    <step num="2">In a medium bowl, mix the butter, sugar, and brown sugar until fluffy. </step>
    <step num="3">Add the eggs one at a time, then add the vanilla. Whisk until combined. </step>
    <step num="4">Fold in the flour, salt, cinnamon, and baking powder until combined. </step>
    <step num="5">Fold in the berries. </step>
    <step num="6">Transfer to a baking pan. </step>
    <step num="7">Bake for 40 minutes, or until golden brown. </step>
    <step num="8">Cool for 30 minutes before serving. </step>
    <step num="9">Slice and sprinkle with powdered sugar. </step>
    <step num="10">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
